caption: I love Chipotle, but this is the worst Chipotle that I have ever eaten from. They give you half the portion of everything and the food is never fresh. I work closest to this Chipotle, so whenever I order when working a day shift, I have to order through Uber Eats so I can choose another location, so they wouldn’t automatically put in my order with this one. Terrible, wouldn’t recommend eating here.
Listless employees, overcooked tortilla, gristly steak. You can do better, Chipotle!

I had a terrible experience. I just got in to my hotel and have been traveling all day. I just wanted something to be delivered to me. While what the delivery guy did is not directly their fault, I have called for over 20 minutes to get a manager on the phone and absolutely nobody picked up. The delivery guy gave me someone else's food from a completely different restaurant and I spent more than the $12 meal of food that I don't even eat. I just want the situation rectified quickly.

Food is mediocre. Service is unpleasant. Have to question their sanitary standards. And they smelled like pot. Won't be back again.

I have come here about twice weekly for the last year. This place is terrible. They are late to open, never have all ingredients prepared for lunch, will climb over the counter where food is processed to get to work, play loud music full of obscenities, and scam you out of every aspect of your lunch.  Today my burrito was nearly 13$ and consisted of a flour tortilla, extra white rice, double carnitas, and cheese. Zero other ingredients and yet they now charge extra for rice.  I have been a loyal customer since the company was founded in Colorado and continued to eat there despite the rampant norovirus across locations in past years. Never again will I go to a Chipotle.  Follow up: I contacted Chipotle corporate to confirm I should not have been charged extra for this.

Always a pleasure eating here, they have plenty of vegan options. It is refreshing to have them as an options in a sea of unhealthy fast food chains inside the food court. Mexican just seems easy and more whole-foods based than burgers, fries, and the like. Glad they have their rewards program.

I ordered the chicken bowl yesterday. I asked for brown rice. They only had white rice. I asked for peppers and onions and was told: “We don’t have any.” Chicken quantity was less than usual so I asked price of more chicken and girl guessed that it was 3 dollars. It was $2.40 which I paid for. Customer before me got 3 huge helpings of chicken. I don’t think he paid for the extra amount as he said nothing. He might have known the girl who served him. Later at night, I developed stomach cramps, indigestion and diarrhea. I went to the bathroom 5 or 6 times. I only had cereal in the morning. Service was very poor, indifferent, apathetic. I won’t return.

I love Chipolte because their flavors just make sense in any and every combination that you choose. I know they are not an authentic  Mexican restaurant, but they are one of my favorite fast food places.  I always get a burrito bowl, because the burritos are not the easiest to eat since that are stuffed. Their guacamole is very good for a fast restaurant. I compare my guac ratings to the table side guac I've had in Miami where you can alter some of the ingredients...like more jalapenos.

Ordered from the app couple of times recently. The first time, the order was not even received by this store when I arrived at scheduled pickup time. They had to start it by looking at my phone. Today, when I arrived at the scheduled time, I asked if my order was ready, because I saw a few bags at the pickup area next to the cashier. I was told no. During the next 5 minutes' waiting, I didn't see any signs of my order was being prepared and I asked again. This time a different person check the bags and handed over my order. I waited for at least 5 minutes from something already ready. Lesson learned, don't order from the app, anything could be wrong.

I love chipotle and will go to anyone I see. This all happened on the weekend staff, I have heard excellent things about weekday staff. Anyways, staff was rude and didn’t listen to what I wanted. I asked for a burrito bowl and got a regular burrito that had ingredients I hadn’t asked for. At this point I didn’t bother to correct them because they weren’t listening to me before. So I got a fountain drink and the sprite was completely seltzer water, no sprite syrup. They said they had no ice which was okay but I didn’t know they had no syrup too. Overall I’d go back but during the week. Weekend help is hard to find but come on, customer service should be number 1.

I just feel like this location doesn't care about the food ther serving I feel as thought the staff need to get retrained and or fire some staff to put people who actually care in there place I spent $12 on a meal I wasn't satisfied with.
